<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-33-0817 </DOCNO><TEXT>The sequence of events that took place on April 26th 1986 when the Chernobyl-4reactor suffered a major accident is explained. The local human and environmentaleffects as they are known (to 1987) are summarised. The main source ofthe facts is the report of the International Atomic Energy Agency inSeptember 1986. The scale of the radioactivity released in the accidentwas unprecedented and fallout reached most parts of the northern hemisphere.Local contamination was severe and a 30km exclusion zone around the plantwas declared. The effect on the local ecosystems is detailed. The casualtiesof the accident are listed, both short-term and long-term. The long-termeffects are considered. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>